{"title_page": "Kathleen McLaughlin", "text_new": "{{short description|American business executive}}\n'''Kathleen McLaughlin''' an American business executive. \n\nAfter graduating from  [[Boston University]] with a degree in electrical engineering, McLaughlin received a [[Rhodes Scholarship]] to [[Balliol College, Oxford]], where she studied [[politics, philosophy and economics]].<ref name=\"inc\">{{Cite web|url=https://corporate.walmart.com/leadership/kathleen-mclaughlin|title=Kathleen McLaughlin|website=Corporate - US|access-date=2019-11-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/08/08/business/walmart-academy-employee-training.html|title=At Walmart Academy, Training Better Managers. But With a Better Future?|last=Corkery|first=Michael|date=2017-08-08|work=The New York Times|access-date=2019-11-15|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> McLaughlin is executive vice president and chief sustainability officer for [[Walmart|Walmart Inc]]., and president of the [[Walmart Foundation]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/tosv2.html?vid=&uuid=38c31a70-07ef-11ea-b6b0-456ab4dcfbff&url=L25ld3MvdmlkZW9zLzIwMTctMTAtMjcvd2FsbWFydC1mb3VuZGF0aW9uLXByZXNpZGVudC1vbi1naXZpbmctYmFjay12aWRlbw==|title=Bloomberg - Are you a robot?|website=www.bloomberg.com|access-date=2019-11-15}}</ref> She previously worked at [[McKinsey & Company|McKinsey]].<ref name=\"inc\"/>\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*[https://corporate.walmart.com/leadership/kathleen-mclaughlin Kathleen McLaughlin biography]\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:McLaughlin, Kathleen}}\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American Rhodes Scholars]]\n[[Category:Boston University College of Engineering alumni]]\n[[Category:Walmart people]]\n[[Category:McKinsey & Company people]]\n[[Category:21st-century American businesswomen]]\n[[Category:21st-century American businesspeople]]\n[[Category:Alumni of Balliol College, Oxford]]\n[[Category:American women business executives]]\n\n\n{{US-business-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American business exective}}\n'''Kathleen McLaughlin''' an American business executive. \n\nAfter graduating from  [[Boston University]] with a degree in electrical engineering, McLaughlin received a [[Rhodes Scholarship]] to [[Balliol College, Oxford]], where she studied [[politics, philosophy and economics]].<ref name=\"inc\">{{Cite web|url=https://corporate.walmart.com/leadership/kathleen-mclaughlin|title=Kathleen McLaughlin|website=Corporate - US|access-date=2019-11-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/08/08/business/walmart-academy-employee-training.html|title=At Walmart Academy, Training Better Managers. But With a Better Future?|last=Corkery|first=Michael|date=2017-08-08|work=The New York Times|access-date=2019-11-15|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> McLaughlin is executive vice president and chief sustainability officer for [[Walmart|Walmart Inc]]., and president of the [[Walmart Foundation]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/tosv2.html?vid=&uuid=38c31a70-07ef-11ea-b6b0-456ab4dcfbff&url=L25ld3MvdmlkZW9zLzIwMTctMTAtMjcvd2FsbWFydC1mb3VuZGF0aW9uLXByZXNpZGVudC1vbi1naXZpbmctYmFjay12aWRlbw==|title=Bloomberg - Are you a robot?|website=www.bloomberg.com|access-date=2019-11-15}}</ref> She previously worked at [[McKinsey & Company|McKinsey]].<ref name=\"inc\"/>\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*[https://corporate.walmart.com/leadership/kathleen-mclaughlin Kathleen McLaughlin biography]\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:McLaughlin, Kathleen}}\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American Rhodes Scholars]]\n[[Category:Boston University College of Engineering alumni]]\n[[Category:Walmart people]]\n[[Category:McKinsey & Company people]]\n[[Category:21st-century American businesswomen]]\n[[Category:21st-century American businesspeople]]\n[[Category:Alumni of Ba